## 2. Naming conventions

### Files and folders

**Rule: Use underscores (`_`) for all file and folder names. No hyphens, no camelCase.**

Correct: `patient_info.mdx`, `check_in_a_patient/`, `set_up.mdx`
Wrong: `patient-info.mdx`, `checkInPatient/`, `set-up.mdx`

### Images and videos

**Rule: `{mdx_filename}_{sequential_number}.{ext}`**

Number images sequentially in the order they appear in the MDX file. Videos use the same numbering sequence as images.

Correct: `patient_info_1.webp`, `patient_info_2.gif`, `patient_info_3.mp4`
Wrong: `patient-info-1.webp`, `1_patient_info.webp`, `patient_info.webp` (missing number)

### Image format selection

| Format   | Use for                                          |
| :------- | :----------------------------------------------- |
| `.webp`  | Screenshots, static UI images (preferred default)|
| `.gif`   | Animated demonstrations and workflows            |
| `.png`   | Diagrams, charts, images requiring transparency  |
| `.jpeg`  | Photos (use sparingly)                           |
| `.mp4`   | Video recordings                                 |

