## 3. MDX frontmatter

Every page must start with YAML frontmatter enclosed in `---` delimiters.

### Required field

- `title` -- The full page title displayed at the top of the page. Present on every MDX file.

### Optional fields

| Field          | Purpose                                     | When to use                                      |
| :------------- | :------------------------------------------ | :----------------------------------------------- |
| `sidebarTitle` | Shorter title shown in sidebar navigation   | When `title` is too long for the sidebar          |
| `description`  | Meta description / subtitle                 | Blog posts (format: `"Date \| Author \| Role"`), changelogs |
| `toc`          | Enable table of contents (`"true"`)         | Longer pages with many sections                   |
| `mode`         | Page layout (`"wide"` or `"center"`)        | Homepages, landing pages, blog posts              |

### Frontmatter examples

**Standard documentation page:**
```yaml
---
title: "Check-in the Patient"
sidebarTitle: "Check-in Patient"
toc: "true"
---
```

**Blog post:**
```yaml
---
title: "Your AI Assistant for Smarter Patient and Scheduling Workflows"
sidebarTitle: "Personal AI Assistant"
description: "Jul 28, 2025 | Ruzbeh Irani | User Experience Designer, Air"
mode: "center"
---
```

**Homepage / landing page:**
```yaml
---
title: "Welcome to Air by Athelas!"
mode: "wide"
---
```

**Changelog:**
```yaml
---
title: "Changelog"
description: "Stay up to date with the latest product updates, bug fixes, and new features."
---
```

**Minimal page (Insights sections commonly use this):**
```yaml
---
title: "The Denials Analysis Page"
---
```

