## 4. docs.json navigation

### File location and schema

The site navigation lives in `docs.json` at the repo root. There is no `mint.json`. Refer to the [Mintlify docs.json schema](https://mintlify.com/docs.json) for full reference.

### Global configuration

```json
{
  "theme": "palm",
  "name": "Athelas",
  "colors": { "primary": "#F9345F", "light": "#FA5478", "dark": "#FB8DA5" },
  "favicon": "images/athelas_favicon_bkg.png",
  "logo": {
    "light": "/images/air_archive/athelas_light.svg",
    "dark": "/images/air_archive/athelas_light.svg"
  }
}
```

Brand color: `#F9345F` (used for icons, primary UI accents).

### Navigation structure

```
navigation.tabs[]                  # Top-level tabs
  └── tab.groups[]                 # Groups within each tab
        ├── group                  # Display name (e.g., "Fill a Chart Note")
        ├── icon                   # FontAwesome icon name
        ├── tag (optional)         # Role filter: "Provider", "Front Desk", "Admin", "Biller"
        └── pages[]                # Array of page paths (no .mdx extension)
```

### The 4 tabs

| Tab          | Icon                  | Content                                        |
| :----------- | :-------------------- | :--------------------------------------------- |
| Air          | `laptop-medical`      | `air_*` pages grouped by role + activity        |
| Insights     | `money-check-dollar`  | `insights_*` pages grouped by role + activity   |
| What's New   | `stars`               | `master_blogs/` (Product Release, Customer Stories) |
| Changelog    | `bullhorn`            | `master_changelogs/changelog`                   |

### How to add a page to navigation

1. Create the MDX file in the correct `{role}/{activity}/` folder.
2. Open `docs.json`.
3. Find the correct tab and group.
4. Add the page path (without `.mdx` extension) to the group's `pages` array.

Example -- adding `air_admin/manage_your_practice/new_setting.mdx`:
```json
{
  "group": "Manage your Practice",
  "icon": "gear",
  "tag": "Admin",
  "pages": [
    "air_admin/manage_your_practice/practice_settings",
    "air_admin/manage_your_practice/new_setting"
  ]
}
```

### How to add a new navigation group

Create a new object in the appropriate tab's `groups` array:

```json
{
  "group": "New Workflow Name",
  "icon": "icon-name",
  "tag": "Provider",
  "pages": [
    "air_provider/new_workflow/page_one",
    "air_provider/new_workflow/page_two"
  ]
}
```

