## 6. Mintlify component reference

### Card

Cards are used selectively for homepage/landing pages and special callouts. **Do not wrap general content in Cards.**

**Card with icon (homepage/landing pages only):**
```mdx
<Card title="Card Title" icon="icon-name" iconType="duotone" color="#F9345F">
  Card content description.
</Card>
```

### Icon in headings

Icons before H3 headings provide visual hierarchy:

```mdx
### <Icon icon="icon-name" iconType="duotone" color="#F9345F" size={23} />  Section Title
```

Common icon names: `laptop`, `calendar-check`, `filter`, `timer`, `clipboard-check`, `comment-check`, `circle-dot`, `note`, `image-user`, `box-circle-check`

### Callout components

**Tip** -- Smart Tips and helpful best practices:
```mdx
<Tip>
  ✨**Smart Tip:** Your helpful tip here.
</Tip>
```

**Info** -- Neutral contextual information (use sparingly):
```mdx
<Info>
  Important contextual information or announcements.
</Info>
```

**Warning** -- Important cautions:
```mdx
<Warning>
  Important warnings about potential issues or limitations.
</Warning>
```

**Danger** -- Critical warnings (use rarely):
```mdx
<Danger>
  Critical information about potential issues that could cause problems.
</Danger>
```

**Inline notes** -- Use bold formatting for brief notes:
```mdx
**Note:** Your note text here.
```

**Standalone Note component** (for longer supplementary information):
```mdx
<Note>
  Supplementary information that supports the main content.
</Note>
```

### Steps

Use Steps for multi-step procedures that need visual step indicators. Used sparingly; prefer numbered lists for most procedures.

```mdx
<Steps>
  <Step title="Step Title" iconType="duotone" stepNumber={1} titleSize="h3">
    Step content and instructions.

    ![Image Alt](/images/image.webp)
  </Step>

  <Step title="Next Step" stepNumber={2} titleSize="h3">
    More content here.
  </Step>
</Steps>
```

### Accordion

Primarily used for FAQ sections and alternate method disclosures:

```mdx
<Accordion title="Alternate method: Do something else">
  Step-by-step instructions for the alternate approach.
</Accordion>
```

### Columns

Multi-column layouts for homepage or landing pages:

```mdx
<Columns cols={2}>
  <Card title="Card Title" icon="icon-name" iconType="duotone" color="#F9345F">
    Card content.
  </Card>

  <Card title="Another Card" icon="another-icon" iconType="duotone" color="#F9345F">
    More content.
  </Card>
</Columns>
```

For blog index pages (`product_release.mdx`), use `cols={3}` with linked Cards:
```mdx
<Columns cols={3}>
  <Card title="Blog Title" href="blog_slug" img="/images/master_blogs/blog_slug/blog_slug_1.png">
    Jan 15, 2026
  </Card>
</Columns>
```

### Tables

Use markdown table syntax. Bold the first column headers and key terms:

```mdx
| **Term**               | **Meaning**                                                                |
| :--------------------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Lead**               | A potential patient record with key metadata (e.g., referral type, stage). |
| **Reporting category** | Groups stages for reporting purposes (e.g., Converted, In Progress).       |
```

### Images

**Markdown syntax (preferred for simple, full-width images):**
```mdx
![Descriptive Alt Text](/images/air_provider/fill_a_chart_note/medications/medications_1.webp)
```

**HTML img tag (when specific sizing is needed):**
```mdx
<img
  src="/images/air_provider/fill_a_chart_note/medications/medications_1.webp"
  alt="Descriptive Alt Text"
  title="Image Title"
  style={{ width:"48%" }}
/>
```

Sizing guidelines:
- `style={{ width:"100%" }}` -- full-width
- `style={{ width:"70%" }}` -- medium
- `style={{ width:"48%" }}` -- small / side-by-side

Always include descriptive `alt` text. Include `title` for HTML img tags.

Image paths always use the pattern:
```
/images/{role}/{activity}/{mdx_filename}/{mdx_filename}_{N}.{ext}
```

### Videos

**Local MP4 files** (follow the same naming convention as images):
```mdx
<video controls className="w-full aspect-video rounded-xl">
  <source src="/images/master_blogs/feature_name/feature_name_3.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
  Your browser does not support the video tag.
</video>
```

**YouTube embeds:**
```mdx
<iframe
  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIDEO_ID"
  title="YouTube video player"
  frameborder="0"
  className="w-full aspect-video rounded-xl"
  allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
  allowfullscreen
/>
```

**Arcade interactive demos:**
```mdx
<div style={{ position:"relative",paddingBottom:"calc(54.21768707482993% + 41px)",height:0,width:"100%" }}>
  <iframe
    src="https://demo.arcade.software/..."
    title="Demo Title"
    frameBorder="0"
    loading="lazy"
    webkitAllowFullScreen
    mozAllowFullScreen
    allowFullScreen
    allow="clipboard-write"
    style={{ position:"absolute",top:0,left:0,width:"100%",height:"100%",colorScheme:"light" }}
  />
</div>

<div>
  <p style={{ textAlign:"left",marginTop:"8px",fontSize:"14px",color:"#666",fontStyle:"italic" }}>
    Caption text explaining the demo.
  </p>
</div>
```

### Content formatting patterns

**Headings:**
- `##` (H2) for major page sections
- `###` (H3) for subsections, typically with an `<Icon>` component

**Procedures:**
```mdx
**To complete this task:**

1. First step instruction.
2. Second step instruction.
3. Third step instruction.

**Note:** Additional context or important information.
```

**Links:**
```mdx
[**Link Text**](https://example.com)
```

### Component selection guide

| Need                                | Use                           |
| :---------------------------------- | :---------------------------- |
| Structure content on a regular page | Headings, paragraphs, lists   |
| Visual section markers              | `<Icon>` before H3 headings  |
| Helpful best practices              | `<Tip>` with Smart Tip format|
| Neutral informational callout       | `<Info>` (sparingly)          |
| Important caution                   | `<Warning>`                   |
| Critical warning                    | `<Danger>` (rarely)           |
| Multi-step visual procedure         | `<Steps>` (rarely)            |
| FAQ items / alternate methods       | `<Accordion>`                 |
| Homepage or landing page cards      | `<Card>` with icon + color    |
| Multi-column landing layouts        | `<Columns>` with Cards        |
| Screenshots and diagrams            | `![alt](path)` or `<img>`    |
| Video demos                         | `<video>`, `<iframe>`         |
| Definitions or structured data      | Markdown tables               |

